verses.text_plain: Thus the heavens and the earth were finished, and all the host of them.
verses.verse_html: 1Thus the heavens and the earth were finished, and all the host of them.

tokens.text: and all the host of them

verses.text_plain: And on the seventh day God ended his work which he had made; and he rested on the seventh day from all his work which he had made.
verses.verse_html: 2And on the seventh day God ended his work which he had made; and he rested on the seventh day from all his work which he had made.

verses.text_plain: And God blessed the seventh day, and sanctified it: because that in it he had rested from all his work which God created and made.
verses.verse_html:
3And God blessed the seventh day, and sanctified it: because that in it he had rested from all his work which God created and made. ▼
▼ created…: Heb. created to make

tokens.text: that in it he had rested

footnotes.body_html: ▼ created…: Heb. created to make

verses.text_plain: These are the generations of the heavens and of the earth when they were created, in the day that the Lord God made the earth and the heavens,
verses.verse_html: 4These are the generations of the heavens and of the earth when they were created, in the day that the Lord God made the earth and the heavens,

verses.text_plain: And every plant of the field before it was in the earth, and every herb of the field before it grew: for the Lord God had not caused it to rain upon the earth, and there was not a man to till the ground.
verses.verse_html: 5And every plant of the field before it was in the earth, and every herb of the field before it grew: for the Lord God had not caused it to rain upon the earth, and there was not a man to till the ground.

verses.text_plain: But there went up a mist from the earth, and watered the whole face of the ground.
verses.verse_html:
6But there went up a mist from the earth, and watered the whole face of the ground. ▼
▼ there…: or, a mist which went up from, etc.

footnotes.body_text: ▼ there…: or, a mist which went up from, etc.
footnotes.body_html: ▼ there…: or, a mist which went up from, etc.

verses.text_plain: And the Lord God formed man of the dust of the ground, and breathed into his nostrils the breath of life; and man became a living soul.
verses.verse_html:
7And the Lord God formed man of the dust of the ground, and breathed into his nostrils the breath of life; and man became a living soul. ▼
▼ of the dust…: Heb. dust of the ground

footnotes.body_text: ▼ of the dust…: Heb. dust of the ground
footnotes.body_html: ▼ of the dust…: Heb. dust of the ground

verses.text_plain: And the Lord God planted a garden eastward in Eden; and there he put the man whom he had formed.
verses.verse_html: 8And the Lord God planted a garden eastward in Eden; and there he put the man whom he had formed.

verses.text_plain: And out of the ground made the Lord God to grow every tree that is pleasant to the sight and good for food; the tree of life also in the midst of the garden, and the tree of knowledge of good and evil.
verses.verse_html: 9And out of the ground made the Lord God to grow every tree that is pleasant to the sight and good for food; the tree of life also in the midst of the garden, and the tree of knowledge of good and evil.

verses.text_plain: And a river went out of Eden to water the garden; and from thence it was parted, and became into four heads.
verses.verse_html: 10And a river went out of Eden to water the garden; and from thence it was parted, and became into four heads.

tokens.text: and from thence it was parted

verses.text_plain: The name of the first is Pison: that is it which compasseth the whole land of Havilah, where there is gold;
verses.verse_html: 11The name of the first is Pison: that is it which compasseth the whole land of Havilah, where there is gold;

verses.text_plain: And the gold of that land is good: there is bdellium and the onyx stone.
verses.verse_html: 12And the gold of that land is good: there is bdellium and the onyx stone.

verses.text_plain: And the name of the second river is Gihon: the same is it that compasseth the whole land of Ethiopia.
verses.verse_html:
13And the name of the second river is Gihon: the same is it that compasseth the whole land of Ethiopia. ▼
▼ Ethiopia: Heb. Cush

verses.text_plain: And the name of the third river is Hiddekel: that is it which goeth toward the east of Assyria. And the fourth river is Euphrates.
verses.verse_html:
14And the name of the third river is Hiddekel: that is it which goeth toward the east of Assyria. And the fourth river is Euphrates. ▼
▼ toward…: or, eastward to Assyria

footnotes.body_html: ▼ toward…: or, eastward to Assyria

verses.text_plain: And the Lord God took the man, and put him into the garden of Eden to dress it and to keep it.
verses.verse_html:
15And the Lord God took the man, and put him into the garden of Eden to dress it and to keep it. ▼
▼ the man: or, Adam

footnotes.body_html: ▼ the man: or, Adam

verses.text_plain: And the Lord God commanded the man, saying, Of every tree of the garden thou mayest freely eat:
verses.verse_html:
16And the Lord God commanded the man, saying, Of every tree of the garden thou mayest freely eat: ▼
▼ thou…: Heb. eating thou shalt eat

footnotes.body_text: ▼ thou…: Heb. eating thou shalt eat
footnotes.body_html: ▼ thou…: Heb. eating thou shalt eat

verses.text_plain: But of the tree of the knowledge of good and evil, thou shalt not eat of it: for in the day that thou eatest thereof thou shalt surely die.
verses.verse_html:
17But of the tree of the knowledge of good and evil, thou shalt not eat of it: for in the day that thou eatest thereof thou shalt surely die. ▼
▼ thou shalt surely…: Heb. dying thou shalt die

tokens.text: of it: for in the day

footnotes.body_text: ▼ thou shalt surely…: Heb. dying thou shalt die
footnotes.body_html: ▼ thou shalt surely…: Heb. dying thou shalt die

verses.text_plain: And the Lord God said, It is not good that the man should be alone; I will make him an help meet for him.
verses.verse_html:
18And the Lord God said, It is not good that the man should be alone; I will make him an help meet for him. ▼
▼ meet…: Heb. as before him

footnotes.body_html: ▼ meet…: Heb. as before him

verses.text_plain: And out of the ground the Lord God formed every beast of the field, and every fowl of the air; and brought them unto Adam to see what he would call them: and whatsoever Adam called every living creature, that was the name thereof.
verses.verse_html:
19And out of the ground the Lord God formed every beast of the field, and every fowl of the air; and brought them unto Adam to see what he would call them: and whatsoever Adam called every living creature, that was the name thereof. ▼
▼ Adam: or, the man

footnotes.body_html: ▼ Adam: or, the man

verses.text_plain: And Adam gave names to all cattle, and to the fowl of the air, and to every beast of the field; but for Adam there was not found an help meet for him.
verses.verse_html:
20And Adam gave names to all cattle, and to the fowl of the air, and to every beast of the field; but for Adam there was not found an help meet for him. ▼
▼ gave: Heb. called

verses.text_plain: And the Lord God caused a deep sleep to fall upon Adam, and he slept: and he took one of his ribs, and closed up the flesh instead thereof;
verses.verse_html: 21And the Lord God caused a deep sleep to fall upon Adam, and he slept: and he took one of his ribs, and closed up the flesh instead thereof;

verses.text_plain: And the rib, which the Lord God had taken from man, made he a woman, and brought her unto the man.
verses.verse_html:
22And the rib, which the Lord God had taken from man, made he a woman, and brought her unto the man. ▼
▼ made: Heb. builded

verses.text_plain: And Adam said, This is now bone of my bones, and flesh of my flesh: she shall be called Woman, because she was taken out of Man.
verses.verse_html:
23And Adam said, This is now bone of my bones, and flesh of my flesh: she shall be called Woman, because she was taken out of Man. ▼
▼ Woman: Heb. Isha
 , ▼
▼ Man: Heb. Ish

verses.text_plain: Therefore shall a man leave his father and his mother, and shall cleave unto his wife: and they shall be one flesh.
verses.verse_html: 24Therefore shall a man leave his father and his mother, and shall cleave unto his wife: and they shall be one flesh.

verses.text_plain: And they were both naked, the man and his wife, and were not ashamed.
verses.verse_html: 25And they were both naked, the man and his wife, and were not ashamed.
